casebody.data:
Office of Disciplinary Counsel v. Stevens.

[Cite as Disciplinary Counsel v. Stevens (1993), 68 Ohio St.3d 105.]

(No. 93-1815 Submitted November 10, 1993 Decided December 29, 1993.) *106Geoffrey Stem, Disciplinary Counsel, and Alvin E. Mathews, Assistant Disciplinary Counsel, for relator. A. Karl Stevens, Jr., pro se. Per Curiam.

Respondent’s resignation from the Florida Bar was disciplinary in nature. Accordingly, we indefinitely suspend respondent from the practice of law in Ohio, effective August 27,1992. This court will not entertain respondent’s petition for reinstatement in Ohio until he submits proof of his readmission to the practice of law in Florida. Costs taxed to respondent.

Judgment accordingly.

Moyer, C.J., A.W. Sweeney, Douglas, Wright, Resnick, F.E. Sweeney and Pfeifer, JJ., concur.
